tasks.description:
Phase 3: Create and render the shot group indicator overlay.

Create `src/tools/video-editor/components/VideoEditorLightboxOverlay.tsx`:

**Component receives:**
- `indicator` from the navigation hook return value (T2)

**Renders:**
- Fixed-position overlay at `z-[80]` (same layer as lightbox), top-center of viewport
- **Shot group badge** (when `shotGroupLabel` is non-null): colored dot using `shotGroupColor` + shot name text (e.g. '● Intro')
- **Position in group**: '2 of 5' next to the badge (when in a shot group)
- **Position in list**: '3 of 12' — subtle counter, always shown when list has >1 item
- Use `bg-black/60 backdrop-blur-sm` for pill background, `text-white text-sm` for text (consistent with NavigationArrows.tsx:72 which uses `bg-black/50`)
- `transition-opacity` for smooth appear/disappear when crossing shot group boundaries
- Use `pointer-events-none` so the overlay doesn't interfere with lightbox interaction

**Render in VideoEditorProvider.tsx as sibling to MediaLightbox:**
```tsx
{lightboxAssetKey && resolvedLightboxMedia && (
  <>
    <MediaLightbox
      media={resolvedLightboxMedia}
      navigation={navResult.navigation}
      initialVariantId={lightboxAsset?.variantId ?? resolvedLightboxMedia.primary_variant_id ?? undefined}
      onClose={() => { setLightboxAssetKey(null); setLightboxClipId(null); }}
      features={{ showDownload: true, showTaskDetails: true }}
    />
    {navResult.indicator && (
      <VideoEditorLightboxOverlay indicator={navResult.indicator} />
    )}
  </>
)}
```

Keep the component under 50 lines if possible. If it's trivially small, inline it in VideoEditorProvider.tsx.
